Job Description
Senior sales associates work will be working in a retail setting. They are responsible for answering customer questions and selling products to meet their sales goals. They may cover for managers while they’re on break and time off . Senior sales associates usually work evenings, weekends, and holidays.
Senior Sales Associate Duties and Responsibilities
Since senior sales associates have years of experience, one of their primary responsibilities is training new employees on company sales techniques and visual standards.
Senior sales associates are responsible for identifying products that need to be filled throughout the day and coordinating with the stock team to restock those products.
Senior sales associates know the sales floor inside and out. They walk the sales floor each shift to make note of price and spatial changes.
Senior sales associates will be on point when it comes to current promotions, features, and benefits of each product. They also must be able to answer basic questions about how each product works and how long it will last.
Senior sales associates are responsible for leading junior associates in maintaining the company’s visual standard. They also help management make floor moves when visual standards change.
Assist visual merchandiser in changing the sales floor with seasonal vignettes, new product featuring, etc.
Senior sales associates process customer transactions using point of sale software. They also have the authority to process exchanges and returns. They also explain promotions and add on additional items at checkout.
Maintain the cleanliness, neatness and order of sales floor.
Perform monthly Inventory Count of store items and reconcile with management to accurately reflect product counts.
All other duties .as assigned
